WEBVTT

1
00:00:31.875 --> 00:00:32.916
<i>The day I was born.</i>

2
00:00:34.541 --> 00:00:36.666
<i>my grandmother Clara
was able to see my future.</i>

3
00:00:38.166 --> 00:00:41.708
<i>She said that the stars had aligned
to endow me with gifts</i>

4
00:00:42.166 --> 00:00:45.625
<i>that would help me
with any misfortune of fate.</i>

5
00:00:50.541 --> 00:00:51.750
<i>But I came to forget it.</i>

6
00:01:17.833 --> 00:01:19.000
Grandmother.

7
00:02:31.166 --> 00:02:34.000
<i>My grandmother wrote in her diaries
that memory is fragile.</i>

8
00:02:36.625 --> 00:02:39.290
<i>And the course of a life is so brief.</i>

9
00:02:39.291 --> 00:02:42.250
<i>that we don't see
the relationships among events.</i>

10
00:02:44.250 --> 00:02:46.875
<i>And we don't consider
the consequences of our actions.</i>

11
00:03:00.333 --> 00:03:03.040
<i>This is why. from a very young age.
my grandmother filled</i>

12
00:03:03.041 --> 00:03:05.208
<i>hundreds of notebooks. recording her life.</i>

13
00:03:07.583 --> 00:03:09.250
<i>So that 50 years later.</i>

14
00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:12.500
<i>I would make use of them.</i>

15
00:03:13.791 --> 00:03:15.291
<i>So that I could recover the past</i>

16
00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:18.166
<i>and survive my own horror.</i>

17
00:04:19.541 --> 00:04:22.791
THE HOUSE OF THE SPIRITS

18
00:04:44.375 --> 00:04:46.665
<i>My grandmother. Clara del Valle.</i>

19
00:04:46.666 --> 00:04:50.625
<i>always had one foot in this world
and another in the world beyond.</i>

20
00:04:52.458 --> 00:04:54.415
- Hand it over!
- You gave it to me!

21
00:04:54.416 --> 00:04:56.082
You're distracting me!

22
00:04:56.083 --> 00:04:59.374
Hand it over! Hand it over. Luis!

23
00:04:59.375 --> 00:05:01.582
Hey. Mom says to hurry up!

24
00:05:01.583 --> 00:05:03.624
- You gave it to me yesterday.
- No!

25
00:05:03.625 --> 00:05:06.290
Why are you all in here?

26
00:05:06.291 --> 00:05:09.416
I told you to go get dressed. Go!

27
00:05:10.166 --> 00:05:14.375
What about you. Clarita?
You have to get ready to go to Mass. too.

28
00:05:15.833 --> 00:05:16.750
I'm not going.

29
00:05:17.375 --> 00:05:18.291
What do you mean?

30
00:05:19.291 --> 00:05:21.082
Do you think it's up to you?

31
00:05:21.083 --> 00:05:23.000
- Run!
- No!

32
00:05:24.041 --> 00:05:27.208
Do you think the house
tidies itself by magic?

33
00:05:28.083 --> 00:05:29.874
That way. darling.

34
00:05:29.875 --> 00:05:31.874
You're all going to get sweaty!

35
00:05:31.875 --> 00:05:34.875
Nana. help me. please.
I'm running so late.

36
00:05:35.708 --> 00:05:40.583
<i>Clara developed her psychic powers
encouraged by her beloved Uncle Marcos.</i>

37
00:05:41.208 --> 00:05:45.500
<i>an incorrigible explorer who collected
esoteric knowledge around the world.</i>

38
00:05:47.666 --> 00:05:49.082
I'm not going to Mass.

39
00:05:49.083 --> 00:05:51.500
- Why not?
- Because Uncle Marcos is coming.

40
00:05:52.166 --> 00:05:56.415
Sweetheart. Uncle Marcos is travelling.
Far away. Very far away.

41
00:05:56.416 --> 00:06:00.250
Yes. I know. but he's coming.
and I want to be here when he arrives.

42
00:06:00.958 --> 00:06:02.040
Rosa!

43
00:06:02.041 --> 00:06:03.500
- Don't look at me.
- Rosa!

44
00:06:12.291 --> 00:06:13.249
Clarita!

45
00:06:13.250 --> 00:06:15.166
<i>Her older sister. Rosa.</i>

46
00:06:15.833 --> 00:06:19.250
<i>was the only one who truly understood
Clara's eccentricities.</i>

47
00:06:19.708 --> 00:06:22.082
<i>Perhaps because she. herself.
was otherworldly.</i>

48
00:06:22.083 --> 00:06:23.083
Rosa!

49
00:06:28.750 --> 00:06:32.250
This is the best hideout.
The beasts will protect you.

50
00:06:33.458 --> 00:06:35.290
What are we hiding from?

51
00:06:35.291 --> 00:06:37.957
I don't understand
why we have to go to Mass.

52
00:06:37.958 --> 00:06:40.625
Mom says we can talk to God directly.

53
00:06:41.291 --> 00:06:43.708
Right. Can I confess something to you?

54
00:06:44.875 --> 00:06:48.082
There are things in this world
that I don't understand either.

55
00:06:48.083 --> 00:06:49.874
But I've come to the conclusion

56
00:06:49.875 --> 00:06:52.457
that it's because they have no logic.

57
00:06:52.458 --> 00:06:55.166
Aren't you a little too old for this?

58
00:06:56.833 --> 00:06:59.000
If you mean my embroidery. Dad.

59
00:06:59.583 --> 00:07:03.290
I'm not going to stop until
it's the biggest tablecloth in the world.

60
00:07:03.291 --> 00:07:04.540
Come on.

61
00:07:04.541 --> 00:07:05.625
No. stop!

62
00:07:07.125 --> 00:07:08.750
Come on. No more.

63
00:07:14.208 --> 00:07:16.915
- Welcome.
- Hello. how are you?

64
00:07:16.916 --> 00:07:18.832
Thank you. Hello.

65
00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:20.249
Nicolás. it's been a while.

66
00:07:20.250 --> 00:07:22.082
- How are you doing?
- How are you doing?

67
00:07:22.083 --> 00:07:23.790
That's quite an entrance. candidate.

68
00:07:23.791 --> 00:07:26.124
- Mrs. Nívea.
- How are you?

69
00:07:26.125 --> 00:07:28.624
I reserved the third row
so you can all be together.

70
00:07:28.625 --> 00:07:30.624
- Perfect. Thank you so much.
- Go ahead.

71
00:07:30.625 --> 00:07:31.624
Please.

72
00:07:31.625 --> 00:07:33.416
No. let's see.

73
00:07:34.166 --> 00:07:37.040
- Thank you.
- They're watching us more than usual.

74
00:07:37.041 --> 00:07:38.249
Get used to it.

75
00:07:38.250 --> 00:07:41.082
It's going to get worse
once you're elected as senator.

76
00:07:41.083 --> 00:07:43.374
On this Holy Thursday. we do penance

77
00:07:43.375 --> 00:07:47.082
to commemorate the day
that Jesus Christ. God's son.

78
00:07:47.083 --> 00:07:50.624
died for our sins. So. my brethren…

79
00:07:50.625 --> 00:07:51.625
Dad.

80
00:07:52.916 --> 00:07:55.249
It's good that they covered up the saints.

81
00:07:55.250 --> 00:07:57.291
The blood on them makes me sick.

82
00:07:58.291 --> 00:07:59.541
Pay attention. Clara.

83
00:08:02.458 --> 00:08:04.166
Look at Rosa del Valle.

84
00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:06.541
She looks ethereal.

85
00:08:07.375 --> 00:08:08.790
She's an angel.

86
00:08:08.791 --> 00:08:10.165
Or a mermaid.

87
00:08:10.166 --> 00:08:15.375
…our Savior. to save
the criminal named Barrábas.

88
00:08:17.708 --> 00:08:23.165
And now Hell awaits us
unless we learn to repent.

89
00:08:23.166 --> 00:08:24.333
Incredible.

90
00:08:24.916 --> 00:08:26.832
After all this time.

91
00:08:26.833 --> 00:08:30.916
the story of Hell
is still selling like hotcakes.

92
00:08:35.125 --> 00:08:36.416
Why the sad face?

93
00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:39.041
- Do you want me to leave?
- No!

94
00:08:41.708 --> 00:08:43.375
The little girl talks to herself?

95
00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:47.583
I miss you. Uncle Marcos.

96
00:08:48.458 --> 00:08:49.666
Look on the bright side.

97
00:08:50.333 --> 00:08:53.041
Now I don't have to take
a boat to come see you.

98
00:08:53.583 --> 00:08:55.666
I can do it just like this.

99
00:08:56.250 --> 00:08:57.625
Brilliant. isn't it?

100
00:08:58.541 --> 00:09:01.874
"Barrábas! Let Barrábas go!"

101
00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.750
Are you going to
keep practicing your powers?

102
00:09:07.291 --> 00:09:11.000
Many among the living
would like to have our gifts.

103
00:09:12.166 --> 00:09:13.708
You are special. Clara.

104
00:09:14.416 --> 00:09:16.374
You're going to help a lot of people.

105
00:09:16.375 --> 00:09:21.291
A mob of sinners saved Barrábas from Hell.

106
00:09:21.708 --> 00:09:25.415
And when Pilate asked.
"Who should I release?"

107
00:09:25.416 --> 00:09:30.124
the high priests and elders
recommended to the crowd

108
00:09:30.125 --> 00:09:33.250
that they choose Barrábas.
that they save Barrábas.

109
00:09:34.833 --> 00:09:35.708
Clara!

110
00:09:37.708 --> 00:09:40.207
That's why the thief Barrábas was saved.

111
00:09:40.208 --> 00:09:44.582
That is why. you. sinners. do penance.

112
00:09:44.583 --> 00:09:48.165
or spend the rest of eternity
burning in Hell.

113
00:09:48.166 --> 00:09:49.458
To Hell!

114
00:09:50.875 --> 00:09:52.000
So--

115
00:09:55.708 --> 00:09:58.957
Father Restrepo.
what if Hell doesn't exist?

116
00:09:58.958 --> 00:10:00.500
What did you say. child?

117
00:10:01.083 --> 00:10:02.457
What did you say?

118
00:10:02.458 --> 00:10:04.082
If you're not dead yet.

119
00:10:04.083 --> 00:10:06.374
you have no way of knowing
what's on the other side.

120
00:10:06.375 --> 00:10:08.832
- Sorry. Father.
- Wicked impudence!

121
00:10:08.833 --> 00:10:10.665
That child is possessed!

122
00:10:10.666 --> 00:10:11.666
Did you see?

123
00:10:12.166 --> 00:10:13.666
Devilish child!

124
00:10:15.625 --> 00:10:17.583
- Impudence!
- Father.

125
00:10:18.250 --> 00:10:20.874
That child is wicked!

126
00:10:20.875 --> 00:10:24.290
Only a fanatic like Father Restrepo
could still believe in the Devil.

127
00:10:24.291 --> 00:10:26.832
- It's the 20th century.
- Yes. but that's not the point.

128
00:10:26.833 --> 00:10:29.915
The point is. if they find out
about Clarita's abilities.

129
00:10:29.916 --> 00:10:31.499
the gossip is going to start.

130
00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:33.915
My candidacy for the Liberal Party
has gone to hell.

131
00:10:33.916 --> 00:10:35.040
Don't exaggerate.

132
00:10:35.041 --> 00:10:38.082
I can't keep dealing with people
who gossip about my family.

133
00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:39.915
Your brother was already too much.

134
00:10:39.916 --> 00:10:44.124
No. I won't let you blame Marcos
for whatever comes to your mind.

135
00:10:44.125 --> 00:10:46.707
He's a bad influence on Clara.
And now--

136
00:10:46.708 --> 00:10:49.083
Be careful what you're about to say.
Severo del Valle.

137
00:10:49.791 --> 00:10:53.707
Our family is more important
than our personal interests.

138
00:10:53.708 --> 00:10:54.750
Never forget that.

139
00:10:55.416 --> 00:10:57.750
And we love Clarita just the way she is.

140
00:11:06.041 --> 00:11:07.250
Careful.

141
00:11:10.750 --> 00:11:12.457
- Stay still.
- Stop!

142
00:11:12.458 --> 00:11:14.040
- Careful!
- Sorry.

143
00:11:14.041 --> 00:11:15.333
Stop!

144
00:11:17.333 --> 00:11:18.499
Mom. who are they?

145
00:11:18.500 --> 00:11:20.374
- Is it Uncle Marcos?
- Uncle Marcos.

146
00:11:20.375 --> 00:11:21.583
Marcos!

147
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.457
Your brother's here.

148
00:11:24.458 --> 00:11:27.333
I mean… your brother's body.

149
00:11:28.875 --> 00:11:30.499
- No.
- Follow me.

150
00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:31.791
Nana.

151
00:11:41.500 --> 00:11:42.583
Marcos!

152
00:11:43.583 --> 00:11:44.874
Open it.

153
00:11:44.875 --> 00:11:47.915
<i>That is how Uncle Marcos
came home from his final trip.</i>

154
00:11:47.916 --> 00:11:49.165
My brother!

155
00:11:49.166 --> 00:11:51.790
<i>He had died of a mysterious African plague</i>

156
00:11:51.791 --> 00:11:54.790
<i>that made him wrinkled and yellow.
like parchment.</i>

157
00:11:54.791 --> 00:11:56.833
Clarita said he would be coming.

158
00:12:01.958 --> 00:12:02.958
My brother!

159
00:12:22.708 --> 00:12:23.541
Rosa!

160
00:12:26.833 --> 00:12:28.041
A puppy.

161
00:12:31.083 --> 00:12:32.541
- Hi.
- He was saved.

162
00:12:37.166 --> 00:12:38.291
It's going to be all right.

163
00:12:40.250 --> 00:12:41.833
- So small.
- Barrabás.

164
00:12:48.791 --> 00:12:51.791
<i>That would have been
one of the saddest days of her life</i>

165
00:12:52.541 --> 00:12:55.708
<i>if Barrabás hadn't arrived
with Uncle Marcos' things.</i>

166
00:12:56.458 --> 00:13:00.041
<i>and Rosa hadn't been there to comfort her.</i>

167
00:13:05.083 --> 00:13:09.041
Clarita. Uncle Marcos
brought a lot more books.

168
00:13:10.458 --> 00:13:11.291
And look.

169
00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:15.790
He wrote about all his adventures.

170
00:13:15.791 --> 00:13:16.750
Look at Paris.

171
00:13:18.583 --> 00:13:22.125
Hey. maybe you could do the same. right?

172
00:13:22.708 --> 00:13:24.291
Write down your adventures.

173
00:13:25.625 --> 00:13:28.791
Here's a little notebook. It's blank.

174
00:13:29.375 --> 00:13:30.416
Look.

175
00:13:43.625 --> 00:13:45.666
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

176
00:13:59.333 --> 00:14:01.875
<i>"Barrabás came to the family by sea."</i>

177
00:14:02.875 --> 00:14:04.665
<i>And so my grandmother Clara began</i>

178
00:14:04.666 --> 00:14:08.708
<i>the first of her life diaries.</i>

179
00:14:19.708 --> 00:14:22.125
That's called bribery. and it's a crime.

180
00:14:23.916 --> 00:14:26.582
All of the most respected
senators in this country

181
00:14:26.583 --> 00:14:28.791
have gotten their seats
in Congress this way.

182
00:14:30.250 --> 00:14:31.125
But I'm a lawyer.

183
00:14:32.333 --> 00:14:36.500
I protect the laws to prevent
these very things from happening.

184
00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:41.624
The Holy Thursday scandal
didn't play out well for us. my friend.

185
00:14:41.625 --> 00:14:43.625
And we're on the verge of elections.

186
00:14:46.875 --> 00:14:49.833
I promised my wife
that I was going to do this honestly.

187
00:14:50.500 --> 00:14:54.166
Well. if you want to keep Nívea happy.

188
00:14:55.375 --> 00:14:56.458
this is the only way.

189
00:14:57.625 --> 00:15:02.291
No one but you can push
the suffragists' proposals.

190
00:15:03.708 --> 00:15:07.624
We need to talk with real people.
the people in town.

191
00:15:07.625 --> 00:15:12.499
Go door to door. barge into the factories.
really make noise.

192
00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:14.499
If my husband is elected senator.

193
00:15:14.500 --> 00:15:17.249
we'll be able to make those changes
from Congress.

194
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:19.707
Well. maybe if your husband were a woman.

195
00:15:19.708 --> 00:15:21.874
We want others to make changes.

196
00:15:21.875 --> 00:15:25.290
and we don't even think to
remove our corsets.

197
00:15:25.291 --> 00:15:26.207
You take it off.

198
00:15:26.208 --> 00:15:27.250
What?

199
00:15:29.416 --> 00:15:31.582
- Ma'am.
- My little girl.

200
00:15:31.583 --> 00:15:33.500
Look. another letter for Rosa.

201
00:15:34.500 --> 00:15:35.957
Thank you. Nana.

202
00:15:35.958 --> 00:15:36.791
Mom.

203
00:15:37.916 --> 00:15:39.415
- May I see?
- No.

204
00:15:39.416 --> 00:15:40.915
Is it from Ester Trueba's son?

205
00:15:40.916 --> 00:15:43.874
Yes. he got the license for a gold mine.

206
00:15:43.875 --> 00:15:46.915
- He's chipped away for nearly two years.
- Poor guy.

207
00:15:46.916 --> 00:15:48.165
Why. Mom?

208
00:15:48.166 --> 00:15:51.707
Because he's a very determined man.
and I like that.

209
00:15:51.708 --> 00:15:54.500
Because when a woman
is as beautiful as Rosa.

210
00:15:55.541 --> 00:15:57.916
men don't even dare to approach her.

211
00:15:58.875 --> 00:16:00.958
- Two.
- Thank you.

212
00:16:01.833 --> 00:16:02.791
Look.

213
00:16:03.708 --> 00:16:05.332
It's beautiful. Clarita.

214
00:16:05.333 --> 00:16:07.416
- Can we get it?
- Let's see.

215
00:16:22.458 --> 00:16:23.790
Come on. girls. let's go.

216
00:16:23.791 --> 00:16:25.040
Come along.

217
00:16:25.041 --> 00:16:26.832
Always pursuing my Rosita.

218
00:16:26.833 --> 00:16:28.125
Scoundrels!

219
00:16:29.250 --> 00:16:30.666
Come here.

220
00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:36.541
Excuse me.

221
00:16:39.833 --> 00:16:41.083
What's your name?

222
00:16:41.666 --> 00:16:42.875
Who's asking?

223
00:16:44.250 --> 00:16:45.208
Esteban Trueba.

224
00:16:46.375 --> 00:16:48.375
Come along. or I'll get in trouble.

225
00:16:51.958 --> 00:16:55.207
Her name is Rosa del Valle!
And she has no other suitors!

226
00:16:55.208 --> 00:16:56.500
- Clarita!
- Clara!

227
00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:58.875
What are you thinking?

228
00:16:59.458 --> 00:17:00.291
Rosa.

229
00:17:04.958 --> 00:17:06.249
<i>That afternoon.</i>

230
00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:08.457
<i>Rosa came into Esteban Trueba's life</i>

231
00:17:08.458 --> 00:17:11.500
<i>like a dreamy angel stealing his soul.</i>

232
00:17:14.166 --> 00:17:16.874
<i>And from that moment on.
he promised himself</i>

233
00:17:16.875 --> 00:17:19.957
<i>that he would do anything
to become a rich man…</i>

234
00:17:19.958 --> 00:17:21.040
I LOVE YOU.

235
00:17:21.041 --> 00:17:22.791
<i>…and be worthy of taking her to the altar.</i>

236
00:17:32.875 --> 00:17:35.625
Rosa. another letter. Can I read it?

237
00:17:37.250 --> 00:17:38.707
"My beloved. beautiful Rosa."

238
00:17:38.708 --> 00:17:40.083
- "Every second--"
- Give me that.

239
00:17:41.500 --> 00:17:44.250
"Every second here
is an eternity without you."

240
00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:47.915
I want someone to love me
like Esteban loves Rosa.

241
00:17:47.916 --> 00:17:50.999
I still don't understand
what love has to do

242
00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:53.165
with chipping away at rocks
in order to get rich.

243
00:17:53.166 --> 00:17:54.416
Because he loves you.

244
00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:56.124
I don't want gold.

245
00:17:56.125 --> 00:17:57.207
Neither do I.

246
00:17:57.208 --> 00:17:59.833
But don't you want someone
to give you a house like this one?

247
00:18:00.375 --> 00:18:02.583
- No.
- Then what?

248
00:18:03.583 --> 00:18:05.790
Do you want to live off
your imaginary animals?

249
00:18:05.791 --> 00:18:06.750
Perhaps.

250
00:18:07.541 --> 00:18:08.832
I want that too.

251
00:18:08.833 --> 00:18:10.457
I don't understand you.

252
00:18:10.458 --> 00:18:12.041
Would you like that too?

253
00:18:21.833 --> 00:18:23.041
Barrabás!

254
00:18:23.291 --> 00:18:26.665
<i>For Clara.
time passed with no greater news</i>

255
00:18:26.666 --> 00:18:29.875
<i>than the unlimited capacity for growth
of her dog. Barrabás.</i>

256
00:18:31.916 --> 00:18:32.915
Over there!

257
00:18:32.916 --> 00:18:36.249
<i>Popular fantasies
and lack of knowledge of his breed</i>

258
00:18:36.250 --> 00:18:39.083
<i>eventually credited him
with mythological attributes.</i>

259
00:18:41.375 --> 00:18:42.457
{\an8}<i>Everyone loved him.</i>

260
00:18:42.458 --> 00:18:43.582
{\an8}WINNERS
SEVERO DEL VALLE

261
00:18:43.583 --> 00:18:46.000
{\an8}<i>Except the new senator. Severo del Valle.</i>

262
00:18:46.583 --> 00:18:48.540
Beast from hell!

263
00:18:48.541 --> 00:18:49.916
<i>And Nana.</i>

264
00:19:40.916 --> 00:19:42.166
Someone's going to die.

265
00:19:46.291 --> 00:19:47.375
What's wrong. dear?

266
00:19:48.958 --> 00:19:50.249
Someone else is going to die.

267
00:19:50.250 --> 00:19:51.083
What?

268
00:19:53.416 --> 00:19:56.208
No. my love. don't worry.
That's not going to happen.

269
00:19:57.208 --> 00:20:00.665
But Clara said I was going to fall
off the horse. and it did happen.

270
00:20:00.666 --> 00:20:05.166
Do me the honor of congratulating
the new Senator of this Republic.

271
00:20:08.666 --> 00:20:10.665
You look like you've seen a ghost.

272
00:20:10.666 --> 00:20:13.500
Change those faces.
Today is a day for celebration.

273
00:20:14.166 --> 00:20:15.624
More gifts.

274
00:20:15.625 --> 00:20:19.624
This brandy and a suckling pig
from your southern constituents.

275
00:20:19.625 --> 00:20:21.915
I'll have to travel to thank them.

276
00:20:21.916 --> 00:20:23.583
No! Don't go.

277
00:20:24.750 --> 00:20:27.540
- What's the matter with you?
- I'll explain later.

278
00:20:27.541 --> 00:20:30.458
That's it. Carefully. don't drop it.

279
00:20:33.583 --> 00:20:35.541
It's a huge animal.

280
00:21:35.208 --> 00:21:40.000
Severo. Everyone. if you could come
and listen to our new senator.

281
00:21:46.541 --> 00:21:47.666
Thank you.

282
00:21:48.416 --> 00:21:51.500
Thank you all for being here
to celebrate with me.

283
00:21:52.125 --> 00:21:55.541
Although I should really thank
the dearth of candidates.

284
00:21:58.041 --> 00:21:58.875
Mom.

285
00:21:59.333 --> 00:22:01.374
I don't want anything to happen to Dad.

286
00:22:01.375 --> 00:22:03.832
No. it's going to be all right.
Don't worry.

287
00:22:03.833 --> 00:22:06.540
It's an honor for me to represent
the Liberal Party in Congress.

288
00:22:06.541 --> 00:22:08.750
Let's check out dessert.

289
00:22:09.583 --> 00:22:13.124
As you all know. I've had the good fortune
to live a life of privilege…

290
00:22:13.125 --> 00:22:15.290
How delicious.

291
00:22:15.291 --> 00:22:17.832
…and the time has come to pay it back.

292
00:22:17.833 --> 00:22:18.874
Strawberries.

293
00:22:18.875 --> 00:22:21.915
- I want this one.
- I hope that you've enjoyed your meal.

294
00:22:21.916 --> 00:22:24.832
and that you go back for seconds.
for our own sake.

295
00:22:24.833 --> 00:22:27.666
or else we'll be eating
southern pig for a week!

296
00:22:29.583 --> 00:22:31.958
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

297
00:22:32.250 --> 00:22:33.540
Long live!

298
00:22:33.541 --> 00:22:34.750
Congratulations.

299
00:22:35.333 --> 00:22:36.791
- Long live the Senator!
- Long live!

300
00:22:37.291 --> 00:22:38.750
Long live!

301
00:22:48.208 --> 00:22:49.291
No!

302
00:22:52.500 --> 00:22:54.750
Calm down.

303
00:23:11.875 --> 00:23:13.583
I don't want anyone else to die.

304
00:23:14.291 --> 00:23:17.666
Don't worry. It was a nightmare.
Come. Go back to sleep.

305
00:23:18.333 --> 00:23:20.000
Can you stay with me?

306
00:23:20.583 --> 00:23:22.125
Yes. make some room for me.

307
00:23:26.375 --> 00:23:27.458
It's so cold.

308
00:23:33.041 --> 00:23:35.291
I'm with you always. all right?

309
00:23:36.583 --> 00:23:38.083
Always.

310
00:23:44.750 --> 00:23:46.041
That little hand.

311
00:23:54.166 --> 00:23:55.125
It's a common cold.

312
00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:57.665
See? I told you.

313
00:23:57.666 --> 00:24:01.290
Give her some lemonade with sugar
and liquor to sweat out the fever.

314
00:24:01.291 --> 00:24:03.958
Nana. give her the new brandy
they gave me.

315
00:24:04.708 --> 00:24:06.625
Thank you for coming so quickly.

316
00:24:07.208 --> 00:24:08.541
I'll walk you to the door.

317
00:24:27.875 --> 00:24:32.749
<i>That same day. after a long period
of loneliness and hard work.</i>

318
00:24:32.750 --> 00:24:35.916
<i>Esteban Trueba got
what he so badly wanted.</i>

319
00:24:46.791 --> 00:24:50.750
<i>Finally. he could fulfill his dream
of marrying Rosa.</i>

320
00:24:53.125 --> 00:24:54.957
Give me the red thread. please.

321
00:24:54.958 --> 00:24:58.166
Nana. Barrabás is going to go
on the tablecloth.

322
00:24:59.250 --> 00:25:02.415
Any moment now.
that beast is going to grow horns.

323
00:25:02.416 --> 00:25:03.416
And wings.

324
00:25:03.916 --> 00:25:04.750
Thank you.

325
00:25:05.916 --> 00:25:07.416
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

326
00:25:08.500 --> 00:25:09.666
Drink all of it.

327
00:25:15.083 --> 00:25:16.041
All right.

328
00:25:16.833 --> 00:25:17.708
Thank you. Nana.

329
00:26:17.666 --> 00:26:19.833
What are you doing there. Clarita?

330
00:26:22.083 --> 00:26:23.791
Why is it so dark? What's wrong?

331
00:26:25.708 --> 00:26:28.208
Why does it smell so much of roses?

332
00:26:32.250 --> 00:26:33.250
Rosita?

333
00:26:36.250 --> 00:26:37.250
Darling?

334
00:26:38.125 --> 00:26:38.958
Rosa.

335
00:26:40.958 --> 00:26:41.791
Oh. my God!

336
00:26:46.625 --> 00:26:47.750
Mrs. Nívea!

337
00:26:48.625 --> 00:26:49.583
Mr. Severo.

338
00:26:50.250 --> 00:26:52.000
Mr. Severo!

339
00:27:41.916 --> 00:27:43.250
I'm so sorry.

340
00:27:44.625 --> 00:27:46.625
This was not caused by a mere fever.

341
00:27:49.500 --> 00:27:52.375
Do you remember if Rosa did
anything out of the ordinary

342
00:27:52.791 --> 00:27:55.625
or ate anything that the others didn't?

343
00:27:56.458 --> 00:28:00.250
Nothing. I don't know.

344
00:28:01.625 --> 00:28:06.207
That lemonade you told me to give her
with a dash of brandy.

345
00:28:06.208 --> 00:28:07.041
Clarita.

346
00:28:12.375 --> 00:28:14.333
- It was all my fault.
- No.

347
00:28:15.375 --> 00:28:18.333
It wasn't your fault.
Don't ever say that again.

348
00:28:19.166 --> 00:28:20.000
Promise me.

349
00:28:47.291 --> 00:28:48.999
I didn't expect you to be here so soon.

350
00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:50.166
Good afternoon.

351
00:28:54.666 --> 00:28:55.666
Here.

352
00:29:17.750 --> 00:29:19.540
TELEGRAM FROM THE STATE
ESTEBAN TRUEBA

353
00:29:19.541 --> 00:29:22.708
ESTEBAN. YOU MUST RETURN.
ROSA IS DEAD. FÉRULA

354
00:29:25.250 --> 00:29:27.958
I have my suspicions
that this killed your daughter.

355
00:29:29.083 --> 00:29:30.124
I don't understand.

356
00:29:30.125 --> 00:29:32.958
I need your authorization
to perform an autopsy.

357
00:29:39.333 --> 00:29:41.582
Are you telling me
you have to cut her open?

358
00:29:41.583 --> 00:29:43.375
No. not completely.

359
00:29:43.958 --> 00:29:45.415
Her head will be untouched.

360
00:29:45.416 --> 00:29:48.624
But to do that.
I need to take Rosa to the morgue.

361
00:29:48.625 --> 00:29:49.958
To the morgue?

362
00:29:52.333 --> 00:29:53.458
Not the morgue.

363
00:29:54.125 --> 00:29:55.958
- No.
- Okay.

364
00:29:56.541 --> 00:29:58.791
- No one will take my daughter.
- Okay. Nívea.

365
00:30:00.041 --> 00:30:01.416
Yes. That's how it will be.

366
00:30:02.916 --> 00:30:03.916
You swear?

367
00:30:04.416 --> 00:30:07.333
- Swear it. Swear it to me.
- Yes.

368
00:30:15.666 --> 00:30:16.708
My love.

369
00:30:20.083 --> 00:30:21.665
Don't touch her.

370
00:30:21.666 --> 00:30:23.083
- You won't touch her!
- Nívea.

371
00:30:26.833 --> 00:30:29.166
Take this for your nerves. Just a little.

372
00:30:38.166 --> 00:30:39.416
I'm sorry. my love.

373
00:30:40.125 --> 00:30:41.958
I'm doing this for the whole family.

374
00:30:43.791 --> 00:30:47.165
Nana. tell the staff
they can take off the rest of the day.

375
00:30:47.166 --> 00:30:48.124
Yes. sir.

376
00:30:48.125 --> 00:30:50.791
And let Clarita sleep with Teresa. please.

377
00:30:51.583 --> 00:30:53.208
I don't want her to sleep alone.

378
00:31:10.625 --> 00:31:11.458
Severo.

379
00:31:15.875 --> 00:31:17.416
Good evening. sir…

380
00:31:25.166 --> 00:31:26.250
Careful.

381
00:31:39.083 --> 00:31:42.000
There was rat poison
in that bottle of brandy.

382
00:31:43.708 --> 00:31:45.666
Enough to kill a bull.

383
00:31:48.541 --> 00:31:51.958
Now we only need to medically verify
that it was murder.

384
00:31:54.750 --> 00:31:56.500
She needs to be undressed. Severo.

385
00:32:13.166 --> 00:32:14.541
I'm sorry. my child.

386
00:32:45.916 --> 00:32:47.791
I can't watch this.

387
00:33:11.916 --> 00:33:12.916
Rosa?

388
00:33:21.791 --> 00:33:22.625
Sir?

389
00:33:23.541 --> 00:33:24.916
Where is Rosa?

390
00:33:28.833 --> 00:33:29.875
Sir…

391
00:33:32.916 --> 00:33:34.083
With the doctor.

392
00:33:35.166 --> 00:33:36.083
In the kitchen.

393
00:33:37.791 --> 00:33:39.583
Stay here. please.

394
00:33:40.250 --> 00:33:41.166
Stay.

395
00:33:42.125 --> 00:33:45.083
Have a drink. please.

396
00:33:49.000 --> 00:33:50.000
Sit.

397
00:33:51.416 --> 00:33:52.291
Sit.

398
00:34:18.500 --> 00:34:19.333
Thank you.

399
00:34:21.458 --> 00:34:22.666
It was my fault. Nana.

400
00:34:23.666 --> 00:34:24.916
It was my fault.

401
00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:28.625
I should be the one dead.

402
00:34:29.458 --> 00:34:31.791
- Don't say that.
- Not my Rosa.

403
00:34:38.416 --> 00:34:39.250
Nana.

404
00:35:08.708 --> 00:35:09.666
Poor girl.

405
00:35:10.250 --> 00:35:12.000
This was meant for Severo.

406
00:35:12.458 --> 00:35:13.791
I have to warn him.

407
00:35:21.333 --> 00:35:22.708
I'm quitting politics.

408
00:35:23.291 --> 00:35:24.958
I'm quitting the Liberal Party.

409
00:35:25.666 --> 00:35:27.000
All that shit.

410
00:35:40.916 --> 00:35:44.750
May no one in my family
ever get involved in politics again.

411
00:37:10.375 --> 00:37:14.000
<i>My grandmother Clara felt
all the emptiness of the world inside her.</i>

412
00:37:15.958 --> 00:37:18.291
<i>The silence filled her completely</i>

413
00:37:30.250 --> 00:37:34.333
<i>and she wouldn't say another word
until nine years later.</i>

414
00:37:42.333 --> 00:37:45.457
<i>Rosa's murder was the first
of many acts of violence</i>

415
00:37:45.458 --> 00:37:48.374
<i>that my family was destined to experience.</i>

416
00:37:48.375 --> 00:37:50.207
The Lord is with you.

417
00:37:50.208 --> 00:37:52.999
Blessed are you among all women

418
00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:55.832
and blessed is the fruit
of your womb. Jesus.

419
00:37:55.833 --> 00:37:56.915
Holy Mary…

420
00:37:56.916 --> 00:38:02.000
The truth is.
someone tried to assassinate Severo.

421
00:38:02.666 --> 00:38:06.000
<i>The police tried to find the source
of the poisoned bottle.</i>

422
00:38:06.291 --> 00:38:11.040
<i>but neither they nor the private detective
hired by my great-grandfather Severo.</i>

423
00:38:11.041 --> 00:38:13.374
<i>were able to find the murderers.</i>

424
00:38:13.375 --> 00:38:17.208
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners…

425
00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:20.250
<i>And the shadow
of that unresolved vengeance</i>

426
00:38:20.875 --> 00:38:23.374
<i>remained present
in subsequent generations.</i>

427
00:38:23.375 --> 00:38:26.499
Full of grace you are.
The Lord is with you.

428
00:38:26.500 --> 00:38:29.290
Blessed are you among all women

429
00:38:29.291 --> 00:38:32.124
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb. Jesus.

430
00:38:32.125 --> 00:38:37.249
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners.

431
00:38:37.250 --> 00:38:40.333
now and at the hour of our death. amen.

432
00:38:52.291 --> 00:38:53.458
Clarita.

433
00:38:58.666 --> 00:38:59.833
Clarita. my love.

434
00:39:02.750 --> 00:39:04.750
Come and say goodbye to your sister.

435
00:39:12.833 --> 00:39:15.083
This didn't happen because you said so.

436
00:39:15.750 --> 00:39:19.833
You may be able to predict things.
but you can't stop them from happening.

437
00:39:29.416 --> 00:39:30.916
Little angel.

438
00:39:36.625 --> 00:39:38.250
Where do you have her?

439
00:39:39.250 --> 00:39:40.375
I want to see her!

440
00:39:41.791 --> 00:39:42.750
Where is she?

441
00:39:43.416 --> 00:39:44.625
Rosa!

442
00:39:45.958 --> 00:39:47.000
Rosa!

443
00:40:18.375 --> 00:40:19.833
My Rosa.

444
00:40:24.250 --> 00:40:26.416
I'm sorry for not fulfilling my promise.

445
00:40:27.458 --> 00:40:29.250
It was out of my hands.

446
00:40:31.041 --> 00:40:32.416
I'm sorry.

447
00:40:33.708 --> 00:40:35.625
Come with us to the burial. Esteban.

448
00:40:43.916 --> 00:40:46.166
Why can't we go?

449
00:40:49.708 --> 00:40:52.375
The burial service is for men only.

450
00:41:05.166 --> 00:41:06.291
Clarita!

451
00:41:10.708 --> 00:41:11.957
Stop the car!

452
00:41:11.958 --> 00:41:13.291
What are you doing. my dear?

453
00:41:15.791 --> 00:41:17.208
Come here. my love.

454
00:41:39.583 --> 00:41:40.916
You're Clara?

455
00:41:43.750 --> 00:41:46.166
Rosa mentioned you in many of her letters.

456
00:41:48.375 --> 00:41:49.750
How old are you?

457
00:41:56.458 --> 00:41:58.000
Clara. why don't you speak?

458
00:42:00.791 --> 00:42:05.541
<i>Clara maintained her silence.
but in that moment she knew</i>

459
00:42:06.375 --> 00:42:08.875
<i>that her destiny
and that of Esteban Trueba</i>

460
00:42:10.291 --> 00:42:12.291
<i>would be linked forever.</i>
